        <descriptionSet>
            <description>Artist, Claire Van Vliet created this work using die –cut colored Navaho paper and acetate. By mixing and re-arranging the 39 items one can create a myriad of landscapes each evoking their own feeling.  This book invites the reader to create their own “landscape” encouraging them to interpret their surroundings as they see it. In 1966 she settled in rural Vermont far from the mainstreams of contemporary life it is this landscape that has had a great impact on Van Vliet’s work.  </description>
